
// The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [validators.mandatory] slot in Hyperlambda. This slot is used to ensure that a specific argument, in this case, [type], is provided in the [.arguments] node set. If the [type] argument is not supplied, the [validators.mandatory] slot will throw an exception, indicating that the argument is required. This is useful for enforcing mandatory input parameters in a Hyperlambda application.
validators.mandatory:x:@.arguments/*/type
